Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Property dispatch (not captured by the graph)", "Subsection",
 CellID->212,ExpressionUUID->"87b4bf4f-8cd8-4156-88de-56b5e0948230"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Every paclet object responds to property-string queries: ",
 StyleBox["qs[\"DensityMatrix\"]", "Input",
  FontFamily->"Source Code Pro"],
 " returns a matrix, ",
 StyleBox["qs[\"NormalizedState\"]", "Input",
  FontFamily->"Source Code Pro"],
 " returns a fresh ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["QuantumState", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "72cf2bd6-6603-4a7e-9ef7-0e4e8886e600"],
 ", and so on. These are runtime accessors, not constructor calls, so they \
don't appear as edges in the function-graph by design \[LongDash] the graph \
is about ",
 StyleBox["object-to-object",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " composition, not property lookup. Still, the writer of a ref page \
documents them; here is a quick survey on a Bell state:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c24b656f-d229-432b-a8e3-a4148ad7de43"],

